      "source": [
        "##Interpretation:\n",
        "* **vs original label** drops as noise increases because some readings genuinely\n",
        "  cross a decision boundary (e.g. soil moisture noise pushes a borderline THIRST\n",
        "  reading to SAFE) — this is EXPECTED and not a model failure.\n",
        "* **vs recomputed label** shows whether the model still makes the CORRECT decision\n",
        "  for the new (noisy) sensor conditions — this is the more honest robustness metric.\n",
        "* A 1.0x multiplier represents realistic sensor tolerance straight from the datasheets."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jckwhKph_OhD"
      },
      "id": "jckwhKph_OhD"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Confusion matrix at realistic (1.0x) sensor noise — the most representative demo-day scenario\n",
        "scaled_noise = noise_levels  # 1.0x\n",
        "X_test_noisy = add_sensor_noise(X_test, scaled_noise)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Air_Temp_C'] = X_test_noisy['Air_Temp_C'].clip(10, 50)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Air_Humidity_Pct'] = X_test_noisy['Air_Humidity_Pct'].clip(2, 100)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Solar_Radiation_W_m2'] = X_test_noisy['Solar_Radiation_W_m2'].clip(0, 1100)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Soil_Moisture_Pct'] = X_test_noisy['Soil_Moisture_Pct'].clip(0, 100)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Root_Temp_C'] = X_test_noisy['Root_Temp_C'].clip(5, 55)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['Tank_Level_Pct'] = X_test_noisy['Tank_Level_Pct'].clip(0, 100)\n",
        "X_test_noisy['VPD_kPa'] = recompute_vpd(X_test_noisy)\n",
        "\n",
        "true_labels_noisy = X_test_noisy.apply(relabel, axis=1)\n",
        "y_pred_noisy = final_model.predict(X_test_noisy[feature_cols])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"=== Realistic Sensor Noise (1.0x datasheet tolerance) ===\")\n",
        "print(classification_report(true_labels_noisy, y_pred_noisy, digits=4))\n",
        "\n",
        "cm_noisy = confusion_matrix(true_labels_noisy, y_pred_noisy, labels=labels_order)\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,5))\n",
        "disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm_noisy, display_labels=labels_order)\n",
        "disp.plot(ax=ax, cmap='Oranges', colorbar=True, values_format='d')\n",
        "plt.title('Confusion Matrix Under Realistic Sensor Noise')\n",
        "plt.show()"
