        "### Loading the model on the Raspberry Pi\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "model = joblib.load('climashield_random_forest.joblib')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Build one row from live sensor readings (same column order as training)\n",
        "sample = pd.DataFrame([{\n",
        "    'Air_Temp_C': 41.2,\n",
        "    'Air_Humidity_Pct': 14.0,\n",
        "    'Solar_Radiation_W_m2': 780.0,\n",
        "    'Soil_Moisture_Pct': 28.0,\n",
        "    'Root_Temp_C': 44.0,\n",
        "    'VPD_kPa': 5.9,\n",
        "    'Tank_Level_Pct': 55.0\n",
        "}])\n",
        "\n",
        "status = model.predict(sample)[0]   # 'SAFE' / 'HEAT' / 'THIRST'\n",
        "print(status)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Make sure the Pi's Python environment has the **same scikit-learn version** used here in Colab (mismatched versions can cause `joblib.load` warnings or errors). Check the version with the cell below and pin it on the Pi with `pip install scikit-learn==<version>`.\n"
